<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Sweepstakes Site Types Explained | SafeTracker: Sweepstakes</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Definitions of the sweepstakes, rewards, directory, sample, and lead-generation site types used by SafeTracker: Sweepstakes.">
  <meta name="robots" content="index,follow,max-image-preview:large,max-snippet:-1">
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://sweeps.safetrackerhub.com/site-types">
  <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="assets/safetracker-icon.png">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/site.css">
</head>
<body>
  <header class="site-header review-site-header">
    <div class="review-shell review-masthead">
      <a class="review-brand" href="index.html#rankings">← SafeTracker: Sweepstakes</a>
      <span>Tracker glossary</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <main class="review-shell review-main">
    <p class="section-kicker">Tracker glossary</p>
    <h1 class="section-title">Sweepstakes site types explained</h1>
    <p class="type-intro">A site’s type describes how it operates—not whether it is trustworthy. ScamFactor separately measures risk and friction. Use these definitions to understand what you are comparing.</p>
    <div class="type-grid">
      {% for type_name, description in site_types.items() %}
        {% if type_examples[type_name] %}
        <section class="type-card" id="{{ type_name }}">
          <h2>{{ type_name|replace('-', ' ')|title }}</h2>
          <p>{{ description }}</p>
          <p class="type-examples">Examples in this tracker: {{ type_examples[type_name]|join(', ') }}</p>
        </section>
        {% endif %}
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </main>
  <footer class="site-footer">
    <div class="review-shell footer-bottom">Definitions last refreshed {{ last_updated }} · Site type and ScamFactor measure different things.</div>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
